Linear regression

.

.

$$ Y = \theta_0 + \theta_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta_p X_p + \epsilon $$

$\theta_0, \theta_1, \cdots, \theta_p$, .

$\theta_0$ $p+1$ .

$x_{ij}$ $N \times (p+1)$ $\mathbf{X}$ .

$$ \mathbf{X} = \begin{bmatrix} x_{10} & x_{11} & \cdots & x_{1p}\\ x_{20} & x_{21} & \cdots & x_{2p}\\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\ x_{N0} & x_{N1} & \cdots & x_{Np} \end{bmatrix} $$

$i$ $x_i$ $p+1$ , $x_{i0} = 1 $ .

.

.

$$ \hat{\boldsymbol{\theta}} = (\mathbf{X}^{\top}\mathbf{X})^{-1} \mathbf{X}^{\top} \mathbf{y} $$

MSE

.

$$ \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i)^2 $$

$\cdot$ , $x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} = x_i^{\top} \boldsymbol{\theta} $.

MSE (Mean Squared Error) , ($L_2$ ) $\boldsymbol{\theta}$ .

$\boldsymbol{\theta} = \begin{bmatrix}\theta_0 & \theta_1 & \cdots & \theta_p \end{bmatrix}^{\top}$ , $\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$ $\theta_0, \theta_1, \cdots, \theta_p$ .

, $\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$ $\mathbf{X}, \mathbf{y}$ .

(GD, Gradient Descent)

.

, $\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$ $\mathbf{X}, \mathbf{y}$ , $\theta_0, \theta_1, \cdots, \theta_p$ .

$\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$ $\theta_0, \theta_1, \cdots, \theta_p$ , .

.

, ($\theta$) .

$\nabla$ $\nabla_{\boldsymbol{\theta}}$ .

$\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$

$$ \nabla_{\boldsymbol{\theta}} \mathrm{MSE} (\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_0} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \\ \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_1} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \\ \vdots \\ \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_p} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \end{bmatrix} $$

.

$$ \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_j} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$$ , $\mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta})$ $\theta_j$ .

graident vector

$$ \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i)^2 $$ .

$$ x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} = \theta_0 + x_{i1} \theta_1 + \cdots + x_{ip} \theta_p,$$ , $$ \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta_j} (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i)^2 = 2 (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i) x_{ij}$$ .

, \begin{align*} \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta_j} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) &= \frac{2}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i) x_{ij} \\ & = \frac{2}{N} \begin{bmatrix} x_{1j} & \cdots & x_{Nj} \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} x_1 \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_1 \\ \vdots \\ x_N \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_N \end{bmatrix} \\ & = \frac{2}{N} \begin{bmatrix} x_{1j} & \cdots & x_{Nj} \end{bmatrix} \left( \begin{bmatrix} x_1 \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} \\ \vdots \\ x_N \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} \end{bmatrix} - \begin{bmatrix} y_{1} \\ \vdots \\ y_N\end{bmatrix} \right)\\ & = \frac{2}{N} \begin{bmatrix} x_{1j} & \cdots & x_{Nj} \end{bmatrix} \left( \begin{bmatrix} x_{10} & \cdots & x_{1p} \\ \vdots & & \vdots \\ x_{N0} & \cdots & x_{Np} \end{bmatrix} \boldsymbol{\theta} - \begin{bmatrix} y_{1} \\ \vdots \\ y_N\end{bmatrix} \right)\\ & = \frac{2}{N} \mathbf x_j^{\top} (\mathbf X \boldsymbol{\theta} - \mathbf y). \end{align*} .

gradient vector . \begin{equation*} \nabla_{\boldsymbol{\theta}} \mathrm{MSE} (\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_0} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \\ \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_1} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \\ \vdots \\ \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_p} \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \end{bmatrix} = \frac{2}{N} \begin{bmatrix} \mathbf x_0^{\top} (\mathbf X \boldsymbol{\theta}- \mathbf y) \\ \mathbf x_1^{\top} (\mathbf X \boldsymbol{\theta} - \mathbf y) \\ \vdots \\ \mathbf x_p^{\top} (\mathbf X \boldsymbol{\theta} - \mathbf y) \end{bmatrix} = \frac{2}{N} \mathbf X^{\top} (\mathbf X \boldsymbol{\theta} - \mathbf y). \end{equation*}

$\eta$ $\eta \nabla_{\boldsymbol{\theta}} \mathrm{MSE} (\boldsymbol{\theta})$ .

$\boldsymbol{\theta}$ $\boldsymbol{\theta}^{\text{(next step)}}$ .

$$ \boldsymbol{\theta}^{\text{(next step)}} = \boldsymbol{\theta} - \eta \nabla_{\boldsymbol{\theta}} \mathrm{MSE} (\boldsymbol{\theta}) $$

    grad = 2 / N * Xb.T @ (Xb @ theta - Y)
    # update theta
    theta = theta - eta * grad
    evolution = np.vstack((evolution, np.ravel(theta)))

MSE .

$$ \mathrm{MSE}(\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i \cdot \boldsymbol{\theta} - y_i)^2 $$

In[13]:
# define MSE
def MSE(theta, X, y):
    mse = 0
    for i in range(X.shape[0]):
        mse = mse + (X[i,:].T @ theta - y[i]) ** 2
    return mse / X.shape[0]

In[22]:
n_epochs = 50

theta = np.random.randn(2, 1)
evolution_s = np.ravel(theta)

for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    
    #        .
    random_idxes = np.random.choice(range(N), size=N, replace=False)  

    for i, rd_id in enumerate(random_idxes):
        
        #  observation 
        xi, yi = Xb[rd_id:rd_id+1, ], Y[rd_id:rd_id+1, ]
        
        # gradient 
        grad = 2 * xi.T @ (xi @ theta - yi)
        
        # learning schedule 
        eta = learning_schedule(epoch * N + i)
        
        # theta 
        theta = theta - eta * grad
        
        evolution_s = np.vstack((evolution_s, np.ravel(theta)))

In[27]:
n_epochs = 50
t0, t1 = 5, 100
eta = 0.01

def learning_schedule(t):
    return t0 / (t + t1)

theta = np.random.randn(2, 1)

batch_size = 5     # batch  
num_batch = N // batch_size

evolution_m = np.ravel(theta)

for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    
    random_indexes = np.random.choice(range(N), size=N, replace=False)
        
    for i in range(num_batch - 1):
        
        selected_idxs = random_indexes[i * batch_size:(i + 1) * batch_size]
        xi, yi = Xb[selected_idxs, :], Y[selected_idxs, :]
        
        grad = 2 * xi.T @ (xi @ theta - yi)
        eta = learning_schedule(epoch * N + i * batch_size)
        theta = theta - eta * grad
        evolution_m = np.vstack((evolution_m, np.ravel(theta)))
